body:
😭 let's maybe finish #1620 quickly and be cautious adding more estimators.
There's clearly some issues not being picked up by our current testing framework.

@lmmentel, I'd suggest, just escape all the failing tests for now, and let's investigate them one-by-one post-#1620.

@MatthewMiddlehurst, regarding the tests, I'm also generally critical of tests that ask methods to arrive at specific predictions up to the x-th decimal. These can be impacted by random number generators and idiosyncrasies of packages or python versions. As long as this is a general problem with the python ecosystem, we shouldn't be tying ourselves too strictly to consistency across versions imo.
